Citation.sTitle: Volumetric, ultrasonic, and viscometric behaviour of glycine, DL-alanine, and L-valine in aqueous 1,4-butanediol solutions at different temperatures
Citation.sAbstract: Densities, q, ultrasonic speeds, u, and viscosities, g, of aqueous-1,4-butanediol (20% and 40% w/w of 1,4- butanediol) and of solutions of glycine (Gly), DL-alanine (Ala), and L-valine (Val) in aqueous-1,4-butanediol were measured at T = (298.15, 303.15, 308.15, 313.15, and 318.15) K.
